Review text:
My favorite mosque in Bandung ♥
It's a very peaceful place filled with some of the most peaceful people too 😇
This mosque is so much more than just a worshipping place, it's an entire complex. The complex has a canteen, a cafe, a bank, a store, charity services, a library, an outdoor soccer field, a wide open grass field, and many more. In the lobby, there used to be a free tea and coffee station (before pandemic times). There is also a power bank rental service, free charging stations, and a few benches to sit and rest.
The toilets and the wudhu area is quite spacious and very clean.
The main praying area is very open and has a beautiful wood interior.
Overall, i think visiting this mosque is not just a destination, it's a whole experience...a blessing experience... 😊
Note: there are so many cute and lovable cats here so prepare to bring some food and many pets for them 😸

Always love the vibrancy of peace and calm there. Learn deeper about Islam and humanity in one package there is easier because we can get all we need at Salman mosque with its integrated system. We can pray peacefully, we can get a lot of foods within the mosque area, we can get free water and tea, we can read books on library, we can participate on islamic event, we can join the charity and funding programs, and we can join organization or volunteering as well.

Best mosque in the entire nation, in my opinion. The khotbah during Ramadhan was always science oriented so it's nice to have logical approach to religion. The place also provide pillow and small mattress for musafir
A good place to worship. Surrounding by tress. Arround the Masjid Salman you may find many Local food as well

a good place. there's a lot of street food vendor and the area is well shielded from the heat of the sun and winds. if you wanted to casually eat, doing some works, or strolling, this place has it all.

If you talk about Ganesha or ITB, then Salman is one must to visit place. It is Mosque, mainly for Islamic praying and activies but Salman Mosque is more than that
It has space where you can just take a quick rest, rejenuvate your stamina and take moment of relax with its calm vibe and softly breeze.
Within the complex, Salman has cafetaria, bank, mini market, and many other facilities you might need.
In afternoon, you could see, many people just lazing around in its wooden or concrete terrace
ps: you need to try Salman special signature, Hot Tea and Hot Coffee
It's an historical mosque, the one that Ir. Soekarno design himself. Place to worship for moslem, but a nice place for meeting and eat too.
It was beautiful place and clean. I will comeback again if I'm visit bandung again
A nice big and magnificent clean mosque ..
A nice place and surrounded by horse riding activity and a lot of street food
Always lovely great place for sholat...
Cozy and warm place for worship and take some rest
Cons= women toilets' cleanliness are still bad
This is the most favorite mosque in bandung. The facility are clean. The peoples around the mosque are very kind
The greatest mosque in the great college
try to strict to covid19 protocol

One of the historical places about indonesian architectural mosque precedent
It was a great place for all of you that wanna pray
One of the best masjid I've ever visited. So spacious yet never empty of people. Great management too.
can't agree more. one of the most lovely great mosque in Bandung.
Very cozy and beautiful place to pray in this Ramadhan. Enjoying hot tea here in the middle of the rain was perfect moment to remember.
The most comfy mosque. Not just a place to worship, but a place for self and knowledge development
A great place to pray w/ university environment... aah!! And the most crucial thing... they have an extremely clean rest room with lot of toilet!!
Masjid salman is the best mosque university in indonesia , i love it

a comfortable and clean place for a campus mosque, with the theme of Friday worship lectures that don't make you sleepy, very good ustadzs often bring lecture here
Comfortable Masjid in Bandung city. Much People pray here and almost fulled in praying time
Good place for praying. The ambience is comfortable.
Feels warm and peace while pray in here
The nice place for pray. When you feel starving you can eat in the cozy cafeteria inside. Healthy and adordable.
Remember my old times here. So solemn and peaceful, good equipment. But you have to bring praying set during pandemic
Iconic building of Ganesha street. Thisbuilding attaches to ITB complex as one of the most respected campus in Indonesia. Functioned as a mosque...
A historical and the most beautiful masjid in Bandung with its non-conservative architecture.

The specialty of this mosque are the floor,  sky, and walls made of wood so that it feels warm inside even though the temperature is quite cool and cold outside besides that, the ablution (wudhu) place are clean, and is available a lot.
The officers who serve the storage of sandals and shoes forced visitors to leave their things.
Randomly visit this place while travelling. You can refill your tumbler, no need to buy a mineral water while you here.
a place that soothes the soul

Beautiful mosque with extraordinary construction. This mosque is among the first to adapt waffle roof construction which can make It's interior strong enough without additional pillar. This mosque also well know as home base for Student Islamic movement and the pioneer of islamic mentorship system in Indonesia.
memorable mosque, I leave a piece of my heart here. always reminds me of my undergraduate years of atudy
Best place to do the itikaf, in ramadhan there is a free playground located in front of the garden. I really miss this masjid.
the place is extremely clean and very comfortable for worship
Always warm and peaceful place I wouldn't miss if I'm visiting Bandung.
Best place to pray around Dago.
Me and my son came here last year and it really great, cz some of the student even playing with my son.

Best place to pray and relax  nice architecture and great program
Open air mosque at center of Bandung city
Calmic place,  with Greenish atmosphere. Comfort point to recharge the spirit.

Amazing mosque overall.
Amazing architecture, with wooden floor and ceiling, it gives warmth when it's getting a cold weather outside.
Beautiful recitation
Especially by the young imams. They are strictly selected to lead the daily prayers here. They have amazing voice.. never be bored when they lead us pray even for a longer duration of praying.
Clean Restroom
You will find dozens of restroom here, however when it comes to a peak hour, you will still find yourself queuing to use it.
Security
The security is standard here. Be careful with your valuable goods. We will never know when the thieves will strike again. A lot had been caught, and punished. A lot recognized by the CCTV and put on a wanted poster. But still there will be a new thief coming.
love to have pray in this Mosque.
May allah bless and protected this msque, so peaceful ....
iconic mosque love to have pray in this mosque

Masjid Salman is the first campus mosque in Indonesia. it is spacious and cool. I used to sleep there. I love the way they package the praying clothes and routinely laundry them so they always smell good.
one of great place to shalat in bandung

big and spacious. also has a big and spacious park in front of it. has more than enough facilities so its well capable to fit more people on special occasions. comes with a cafeteria but the price is quite high. and a few small stores.
Always love praying here except for some unknown strangers asking for anything after a long chat 😅
Very comfort mosque in Bandung. It is clean and spacious. I can drop my baggage in the locker room for free, only donation if you want to give it to the mosque.

I love this place. Wooden floor, nice air circulation makes you really comfort to pray. Canteen and foodstreet along Ganesha would be good choise for you after pray to eat.
This mosque is  also as place to study about Islam for ITB students.
Park are may too crowded on Friday and Weekend due to this place close to zoo.

Really calm, homey, and good ambience. There is free drinking water so you can refill your tumbler there. The toilet facilities are so so, you need to prepare your own tissue and be careful because the floor is slippery.
Muslim worship building in the middle of Bandung city, precisely in the area of ​​the Bandung Institute of Technology. The air is cool. The room of the mosque is spacious and clean

A comfortable place to pray, to study, and to eat (they do have canteen). A wooden floor, a big hall, carpets, everything that makes you warm. It has ground and upper floor. The bathroom is quite big. You are allowed to sleep here if it's late night. You can ask mosquekeeper to keep your shoes. You can have free cups of tea and coffee there. The reason it's only 4 stars is the canteen is a bit more expensive (an average of Rp15.000 for one-time eating).
I always visit this mosque for friday prayer.

A very peaceful and comfy mosque, unique architecture and lots of activity. Never missed praying here whenever I'm in the area. Lots of small bench to sit and wait for your friends or just for chatting while waiting for prayer time to come.

I love the mosque.
Its well maintained and managed.
ITB Alumni is not forget this mosque. Most of them give donation in many ways.
This place gave me inner peace. Always.
Im here n the place very nice
Inspiring place, clean, suitable for praying, meditation, or studying.
The most memorable place in my life

A very nice mosque, with very active community and nice people all around the place. It's also located at a very good location which you can travel to using public transportation.
If you are hungry while you're there, there's plenty of food stalls around, making it also a good place for I'tikaf. At Ramadhan, the place are visited by many people, but it still feels large with a lot of spaces left.
The place are also surrounded by a lot of trees and the air also feels nice. This is a very recommended place, personally.
I love this place and the vibe from this place because this mosque is near from my school

a great mosque with very peace ambience. it has organization that run every business there. it is not merely a usual mosque, it lightens its surroundings. usually many university students come here, but there are others too. citizens like this mosque. the activities also vary. in weekend there's usually bazar or family events.
A beautiful place, not only for worship but also to learn and to eat affordable food
Clean and nice place to do pray
Really cozy comfort place to gather, ear, pray, or even study. You can even study here for 24 hour while in the university library already close
The toilet was on renovation, a right place to rest and enjoy your me time while looking at student activities on daily.
One of the best Mosque i ever seen 😬

One of the oldest campus' mosque and a cozy place to pray. It also has a unique architecture with no pillar on the inside of the praying hall, providing a continuous shaf inside the hall. Cleanliness and the free warm tea or coffee on the outside is also a plus
Nice place for praying and relaxing after doing your activities. Many event held especially on weekend and Ramadhan. Good management and clean.

This is my favorite mosque. This mosque is located in campus ITB area. Full of peaceful. Many people activities such as prayer, recitation, children playing, and other social activity.  The mosque has a unique architecture, with a unique dome. The interior material is dominated by wood. Salman is a spacious mosque but there is no column inside the mosque.

Calming place, the restrooms are nice and clean, doesn't discriminate even if you're walking around not wearing proper clothes (eg: not wearing hijab for girls), you can refill your water bottle for free, could be really cramped during the weekend tho
Nice place with clean atmosphere. There is cafeteria not far from park and you can get a free tea, coffe, or mineral water on the corridor. Free open to all age and all religion.
I always love this place to have a pray.  Because it's so quiet, clean and comfortable. You must be love this place!
One of the greatest mosque in Bandung. It is comfy to pray, and there is free water for all. There is also canteen with a really ok price for University students.
If you want to take prayer, it's one of the best place around ITB. It also has popular foodcourt Kantin Salman which you can buy delicious foods for affordable price there.
Well, a nice place to take some rest
i pray here often.... and the toilet, ritual abulition place was so clean. but remember to place your shoes in the place.

When is time to pray, PRAY!! and Salman ITB Mosque is a great place to Sholah. There are a lot of group and activity to participate around mosque for everyone. Try to deepen your Iman with environment that support you to do so. Plus there are free Tea.

Best mosque ever. Offer sleeping mattresses, pillows, and blankets for anyone willing to stay here at the night. There is water for drinking and even warm tea sometimes. Good for learning Al-Qur'an at evening and college students love to stay here.

One of the nice mosques in Bandung. Not so big but enough space for many activities from salah, reciting Quran, to daily meals. The mosque is vibrant by students' activities and social initiatives. No other similar venues around, so on your trip to lower part of Dago or Jl. Ir. H. Juanda, please consider to also visit Masjid Salman.

One of the most friendly mosques ever. They allow people to sleep at night. Also, the toilet is 24/7 open and clean for everyone. You can even take a bath here decently. There are even some events for families sometimes!
I love the masjid, I spend often in that masjid. Quite, feel serene, and strategic place
Great ambience and one of the historic mosque near ITB!

Quiet place, good for long stay or even resting, full of facility to fullfil your moment of praying.. Restaurant, market, bookstore, zakat centre, and library available for your maximum journey of exploration.

this is how mosque should be, a  community space. Its so lively that you can hear people talking and even kids laughing. They provide tea, coffe and water FOR FREE. Last but not least, they dont prevent you from sleeping, you can even spend your night there if you cant afford a hotel.
A nice place to contemplate. I like to go here if I want to be alone with my thoughts. Even though there were a lot of people at the mosque, I can still find a nice corner to be alone and just relax.

Although I am not a Muslim, I frequently make a visit here.
Salman ITB is not only a mosque. It's like a one-stop place for human activity. There are shops, bank, cafetaria, function room, etc.
Try the cafetaria. It is cheap and has good food. I love to order the frambozen jelly (find it on the entrance). The queue is divided by gender and the canteen is always closed on praying times.
This mosque is very well managed, clean and offers so many activities besides for religious activities.
Good & convenient, especially the canteen where you can find affordable menus!
Never be wrong, that place is masjid Salman.
Famous Legendary mosque in Bandung. Pioneer in mentoring method in da'wah at 1980. Have nurture thousands of young Muslim seeking religious and spiritual way of life since 1980.
So great. Many humble people as well. Feels so comfy
A very modern architecture for a mosque. Love it. MasyaAllah

One oldest university's masjid belong to Institut Teknologi Bandung in Bandung, Indonesia. Circa 1964 moslem scholar and students need a place for shalat. Then finally the masjid was built and the first shalat Jum'at was in Mei 5th 1972.

Wow, I really recommend this place for my Moslems brother and sister. It is a very comfortable place for praying, reading Quran, even for sleeping. There's a lot of Islamic event, almost everyday. If you haven't try to pray in this place, then you have to try. Trust me! It's the best experience ever!

I can say this mosque almost have everything within its area even though it is a campus mosque. This mosque features a canteen, minimarket, services like printing stores, and more.
The prayer room is very spacious and the toilet-'wudhu' is very well maintained. It also has spacious and well maintained front garden.
In addition, they provide free sweet tea and water for public.
I would totally recommend this place to my fellow Moslem friends.
Nice and clean. Especially for woman, there is like locker lady who keep the 'mukena' and we can rent it with free, and for sure she keep it clean.

It is a mosque located in a campus, Bandung Technology Institute (ITB/Institut Teknologi Bandung). This place is quite spacious. It is also clean and tidy. The atmosphere is full of peace and this is what I like the most of this place. The design applied is taking the concept of back to nature by having wooden-like floor design and wooden wall. Besides, the staffs also offer free a cup of sweet tea and coffee for those who need to re-charge their energy.
The place is very clean and very aesthetic. It gives many contributions such as ifthar to everyone who shaum on the day.
The mosque facilities are excellent. You can pray calmly in Salman. There is also wifi in the balcony
A great place to pray, great ventilation, good greenery view in the center of Dago, and the first University Mosque in Indonesia by the great architect Achmad Noe'man and his colleagues.
Clean mosque and got lot to offer.
a mosque that is comfortable, not quiet, and modern. has many toilets and a place for extensive ablution. active mosque, very good
Great Masjid with many religious activities.
Cozy, I mean you can find peace there and the tranquility of it makes it even better... Yeah not your average kind of mosque.

this antique mosque is located just in front of bandung institute of technology. it has a lot of organization that conduct many activities, even for children. the mosque is unfortunately not too large to accommodate the worshipers on friday prayer. on some days it holds islamic study for public.
large mosque and crowded.there are many Islamic events and seminars.
Great place to pray. Huge facilities and quiet for the most of times, except when there are events around holkdays or weekends.
This Masjid still great place to visit.
Good mosque that located at ITB's campus. It's big enough

I am in awe with this place, it so organize. I like how they organize the rent system of kerudung, and it's all clean. The toilet is so clean and the place is all clean. There are many people but it doesn't feel cramped.
Good place to relaxing (at midnight) and studying (at midnight) and of course for pray! There is a free rent mat and/or blanket if you wanna do 'mabit'!
Very convenient to pray here, clean and a good air circulation makes us feel comfortable and not sweating. When Ramadan, we usually get free iftar meal.

Salman Mosque is a mosque built by ITB and other engineers back at that time. This mosque is unique, because usually for a large and wide mosque, engineers tend to put pillars everywhere and blocking praying shaf. Not for Salman mosque, because of the pre-stressed beam technology. I will not explain about that here. Another uniqueness is usually mosques prohibit people from sleeping at any time. Not for Salman, people are free to sleep, doing homework, studying, at least not doing anything breaking the rules. Even in the night, mattresses and blankets are provided to anyone. You can also take free hot tea or cofee, or just plain water. This is one of the best mosque in Bandung
Amazing mosque. There are always millions of reasons to come here.  Again and again.
Big mosque close to ITB campus and Borromeus hospital. Prayer clothes (for women) are clean. A comfortable place to pray

A nice place for doing nothing for sure, waiting for some one,  doing the task, or doing light discussion with friends.
Having a lot of menu in its canteen and quite affordable for student.
Free ifthar food, kurma, and tea in ramadhan. A nice place for spending tarawih here with its imam muda.
But,  its wudlu place for woman quite blek and crowded sometimes.

Good place for kids. The canteen is so cheap and memorable for alumni.
A big mosque in front of the most famous University in Bandung. Experience the unique architecture here.
Best place to chill, eat, and have great knowledge, and obviously pray.

Strategically located in Ganesha st., a legendary street between Juanda/Dago street and Tamansari st.. That's where Bandung is defined, you've not been there unless u step your feet at the are!
Nice place at the ITB complex. Close to Borromeus hospital and there are many food counter. Good Jamaah and always full.
Right in the heart of Bandung, adequate faucets, calming building but it is lack of parking lot.
a comfortable place to pray, there is a cheap and clean student canteen, there is a place where we can take Arabic courses

Cozy, calm, peacefull. But the lighting really dim. Maybe they want you to feel more calm. It's inconvenient to read Qur'an in the night, in the mosque
very nice place for mushafir, there is free drinling water

This mosque is the best place University mosque, bring us nearest to God when you come and feel like that when you out, this place so cold in the morning till morning again, nice place to rest in a day and you can found many people who learn muslim (ilmu agama)

Ow there is cafetaria in front of the masjid.

Nice, vintage, cozy, cool with wood surrounded from floor to roof. The water for WUDHU very fresh !

Simple and minimalistic. Don't expect lavish marble floor or even fluffy carpet -- in fact, Salman has none -- but gotta love it for that reason.
The most comfortable mosque in Bandung. If you are not sure where to go, cone here.

Very efficient. I love the service there where youre supplied with freshly-washed mukenas, and directed to the correct rooms when it gets really busy. Always favoured by ITB kids! There's also a subsidised canteen on the side that sells good food.
really love the atmosphere here, a lot of religious activities, even they provide free tea and mineral water.
Great place to pray, and sometime they provide free drink or food
Comfort place with food and snacks store.  It also have free cofee and sometime also snack
Nice environment and you can get free coffee and tea as refreshment
A lovely mosque to get any extracurricular speech, and even free ifthar :)
I'm so much in love with this place for it gives such a peaceful feeling to me. It's the main worshipping compound at Bandung Institute of Technology.
What a lovely place to pray! subhanallah
Very lovely place to get prayer, but if you want to plane doing jumat prayer you should come first to get the place better
huge mosque. really neat clean, and comfy for everyday prayer

Masjid Salman is an iconic campus mosque located near Institut Teknologi Bandung, Ganesha Campus. What makes this mosque outstanding is not it's building, although it is beautiful, peaceful, and comforting, but it is the people; it is a centre of bustling activities ranging from majelis ta'lim to Arabic language courses to weekend programs for toddlers. The people driving these activities are the best of society, people who dedicate their time for others. I always feel welcome, at home, and at peace whenever I visit this mosque.
Peaceful atmosphere, you won't feel hot in here because of the ventilation system, and tea and coffee services. One of the top masjid in my list
Very good mosque, with wooden floor make it very comfy to pray.
Provides really good atmosphere for praying and other islamic religious activities!
Warm people, cool place to calm down your mind.
Best place to spend time in the middle of Bandung City. Best thing; the toilet is clean.
clean.. many cats.. the floor from woods.. love it..

One of the most comfortable mosque in Bandung. Especially for itikaf in Ramadhan.

This is a great place with halal food surround. It is located in the complex of Bandung Technology Institute.

One of the biggest and historical mosque in Bandung city. Its located in front of the main gate of Institut Teknologi Bandung or ITB and besides the Ganesha park. There are two roads which connected to this place they are Ganesha road and Gelap Nyawang road. This place is so lively because everyday at this place never be so quiet because so many people come to this place, especially the students from ITB. This place is very comfort and relaxing.

This is a historical mosque that proposed by the first Indonesian President. Come and pray inside, then you'll get a true experience of this place.
One of the best mosque in bandung, the floor is very warm due to wooden tile

Quiet place for praying. Canteen, store & park around
One of islamic center of Bandung Moslem Comunity..many scientist & world class of assatidz scholars & speakers

Great place to pray. The conplex is quite large with various facilities: canteen (really cheap!), rooms for student activities, multipurpose rooms, futsal field, rented offices, parking area, and a bank. The yard is huge and green! Always love to pray and relax at Salman.
Well designed Mosque around Campus area, with a lot of people activities every day. Which makes this Mosque so much alive.
Perfect mosque in center of city. Voice of imam are very good.

You can pray here. Masjid salman is clean n friendly.

Lovely public place for Muslim environment, easy access for praying, food culinary, etc. Clean and safe.

Historical place in Bandung, a must visiting  religious tourism spot for a moslem group/family. Sometime good to get self healing or introspection by praying inside this mosque

Lot of memories happen here especially when i was in tpb itb.

Soljum disini, super big and well-managed

Tempat ibadah yang nyaman. Kebersihan yang dijaga. Protokol kesehatan yang dijaga ketat mulai dari masker yang harus dipakai jika kita berada di kawasan masjid, cek suhu, dan hand sanitizer.
Lingkungan bersih, meski sedikit berantakan di beberapa bagian karena ada pembangunan masjid saat saya datang.
Yang saya suka, disini banyak kucing yang sepertinya dirawat oleh pengelola masjid. Terlihat ada dispenser makanan kucing yang selalu diisi penuh oleh pengelola masjid, atau mungkin relawan pecinta kucing.
Keamanan terjamin pula karena ada cctv di banyak sudut masjid.

Tempat ibadah sholat, belajar dan mengaji Al-Qur'an serta ceramah Islam. Sebelah barat terdapat taman Ganesha sebelah Utara taman kampus ITB yang dibatasi JL GANESHA dengan banyak pohon besar sehingga membuat udara sejuk dan segar.

Saya pernah mengalami mimpi Sebelum masjid Salman ITB dibangun dahulunya adalah sebuah surau dari kayu ukuran sekitar 3 x 2 meter persegi. Ketika saya sholat dalam surau ( musholla ) kayu ini tiba tiba angin puting beliung hingga mengangkat surau ini ke langit dan aku tetap sholat di dalam surau ini. Setelah selesai sholat surau ini dikembalikan ke tempat semula dan anehnya surau yang tadinya kecil menjadi besar dan menjadi masjid yang sangat indah hingga membuat saya merasa heran terus tiba tiba saya terbangun dari mimpi.

(Translated by Google) One of the mosques that became an icon of the city of Bandung,
A little history of this mosque
ITB Salman Mosque began to be used in 1972 ago. Initially, the construction of a mosque within the university complex was opposed, because it was feared that it would create jealousy from other groups. However, after receiving the support of a number of lecturers, including Christians and Dutch citizens, the mosque was able to stand with the blessing of President Ir. Soekarno.
This mosque has also been a witness to the student movement. In 1978 ITB was occupied by the army because it refused to re-elect Suharto as president. The Salman Mosque area was also one that was controlled by the military at that time.
------------
It's quiet now, the students are on holiday, the road is too late at night on the block,
remember, always bring a mask here.
(Original)
Salah satu mesjid yang menjadi ikon kota bandung,
Sedikit sejarah mesjid ini
Masjid Salman ITB mulai digunakan pada 1972 silam. Mulanya, pembangunan masjid di dalam kompleks universitas sempat ditentang, karena dikhawatirkan menimbulkan iri dari kelompok lain. Namun setelah mendapat dukungan dari sejumlah dosen, termasuk yang beragama Kristen dan berkewarganegaraan Belanda, masjid bisa berdiri dengan restu Presiden Ir. Soekarno.
Masjid ini juga pernah jadi saksi gerakan mahasiwa. Pada 1978 ITB sempat diduduki tentara karena menolak terpilihnya kembali Soeharto sebagai presiden. Area Masjid Salman juga termasuk salah satu yang dikuasai militer kala itu.
------------
